        <h2>1. Data Processing Overview</h2>
        <p>The app "Fokus-Flow" is a micro-utility tool designed for local habit tracking. We prioritize your privacy by minimizing data collection.</p>

        <h2>2. Local Data (Offline Storage)</h2>
        <p>All core functions (habits, statistics, streaks) are processed exclusively on your device. We do not maintain any servers to store your personal habit data.</p>

        <h2>3. Advertising (Google AdMob)</h2>
        <p>This app is ad-supported. Google AdMob may collect device identifiers (Advertising ID) and approximate location data to serve personalized or non-personalized ads. We use the Google UMP SDK to manage your consent preferences.</p>

        <h2>4. Data Deletion and User Rights</h2>
        <div class="highlight-deletion">
            <p><strong>How to delete your data:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Local Data:</strong> You can delete all data stored in the app at any time by uninstalling the app or clearing the app cache in your Android system settings.</li>
                <li><strong>Advertising Data:</strong> Since we do not use user accounts, we do not store identification data on our own servers. To delete or reset the data collected by Google, please navigate to your Android device settings: <strong>Settings > Google > Ads > Reset/Delete Advertising ID</strong>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <p>According to GDPR, you have the right to access, rectify, or delete your data at any time. For inquiries, contact us via email.</p>
